Jeedom Version 2.4.6

1) Bind device /dev/rfcomm0 to HC05 BT device 98:D3:31:FC:20:FF

sudo rfcomm bind /dev/rfcomm0 98:D3:31:FC:20:FF
sudo rfcomm release all (to unbind all devices)

2) Start mysql database:

sudo docker run --name jeedom-mysql -v /opt/jeedom/mysql:/var/lib/mysql -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=mysqlroot -d mysql:latest

3) Start Jeedom server:

sudo docker run --name jeedom-server \
                   --link jeedom-mysql:mysql \
                   --privileged \
                   -e ROOT_PASSWORD=test \
                   -v /opt/jeedom/data:/var/www/html \
                   --mac-address="02:42:ac:11:00:03" \
                   --device=/dev/ttyACM0:/dev/ttyACM0 \
                   --device=/dev/rfcomm0:/dev/rfcomm0 \
                   -p 9080:80 \
                   -p 9022:22 \
                   jeedom/jeedom

4) Get Container MAC address to avoid loosing API key for Jeedom market

docker inspect jeedom-server | grep "MacAddress"

5) Then, access it via http://localhost:9080 or http://host-ip:9080 in a browser
